Matrix3.Description: A 3x3 matrix with an extra axis in each direction for affine transformations.

Vector3.Description: A 3 dimensional vector < x, y, z > with an extra w axis to make it compatible with affine matrix transformations. Comes with a set of built in vector math operations such as arithmetic, normalization, dot, and cross products.

Length.Description: Calculates the length of this vector.
Length.ReturnValue: The scalar length of this vector.

operator==.Description: Calculates a component-wise comparison of equality with an another vector using epsilon degree of error to account for floating point drift.
operator==.ReturnValue: True if the vectors are close enough to being equal, false otherwise.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be compared with.

operator-.Description: Creates a copy of this vector with the direction flipped.
operator-.ReturnValue: A flipped version of this vector.

operator-.Description: Subtracts a vector from this one component-wise and returns the result.
operator-.ReturnValue: The subtraction between the two vectors.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to subtract.

SquareLength.Description: Calculates the length of this vector squared.
SquareLength.ReturnValue: The scalar length squared of this vector.

Cross.Description: Computes the cross product between two vectors.
Cross.ReturnValue: A vector that is perpendicular to both input vectors.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be dot-ed with.

operator!=.Description: Calculates a component-wise comparison of inequality with an another vector using epsilon degree of error to account for floating point drift.
operator!=.ReturnValue: False if the vectors are close enough to being equal, true otherwise.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be compared with.

operator*.Description: Calculates a copy of this vector that is resized by a scalar factor.

Parameters.Name: scalar
Parameters.Description: The scalar to scale the new vector with.

operator*.Description: Computes the dot product between two vectors.
operator*.ReturnValue: The scalar result of the dot product.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be dot-ed with.

Dot.Description: Computes the dot product between two vectors.
Dot.ReturnValue: The scalar result of the dot product.

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be dot-ed with.

Vector3.Description: Constructs a new 3D vector with given coordinates.

operator+.Description: Adds two vectors together component-wise and returns the result.
operator+.ReturnValue: The addition between the two vectors

Parameters.Name: other
Parameters.Description: The vector to be added with.

Unit.Description: Generates a copy of this vector, but with a unit length of 1.
Unit.ReturnValue: The unit vector that represents this vector's direction.
